{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"body":"Runtime decision cost-verified against the live AWS account (June bill $90.94; rebar's footprint = one t4g.large rebar-gerrit box + Route 53 + free SSM parameters; ECS/ELB/VPC/RDS spend is the co-tenant snap-demo project). REVISED: Fargate/Secrets-Manager/KMS-CMK stack rejected (~$50+/mo new fixed spend); the op-cert service rides the existing box as a compose service (autolander's freed slot, ADR 0047) behind an API Gateway HTTP API IAM/SigV4 front (no fixed fee), key in free SSM SecureString /rebar/prod/opcert-ed25519-key. Zero fixed-monthly-cost increase — a design-time constraint per owner, deliberately NOT an AC. Epic bullet + ee0b + 76d2 updated."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783999889733702001,"uuid":"07b945f2-226a-41ac-85e7-aa785c476ed7"}